<title type="html"><![CDATA[Powerpak stuck at Ciclone screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5988&amp;p=69394#p69394"><![CDATA[
The "tie pin 4 of lockout chip to ground" is the right way to do it, but not really necessary. I don't do it because it seems a tad messy (I can never actually get the pin pulled up!) but if you can, do it.<br /><br /><br />And PowerPaks work with the NTSC consoles, so it's not needed at all. I would bet a decent bit of cash it was his console having a fault connector and the powerpak getting dirty then a actual faulty cart. If I were buying, I'd not worry at all.<br /><br /><br />Hope this helps.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Mon Nov 01, 2010 7:24 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
